{
  "id": "c0c0c0c0-0083-0000-0000-000000000000",
  "name": "Hob↔JS Interop Pitfalls",
  "type": "871ae771-b9b1-4f40-8c7f-d9038bfb69c3",
  "created": 1740873600000,
  "modified": 1774988061511,
  "content": {
    "tags": [
      "bff75873-edb8-412e-81c9-c744e68fe29f",
      "c0c0c0c0-0085-0000-0000-000000000000"
    ],
    "description": [
      ":doc",
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Hob and JavaScript have different runtime models. These pitfalls arise at the boundary and have caused real bugs during Hob view conversions."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Hob Functions Are Always Async"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Every Hob function returns a Promise. Never pass a Hob function as a synchronous callback to JS APIs:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "// BROKEN — Array.find gets a Promise (truthy), matches first element\nconst found = items.find(hobPredicate);\n\n// BROKEN — Array.sort gets Promise comparisons, breaks ordering\nitems.sort(hobComparator);\n\n// BROKEN — getItemName returns \"[object Promise]\"\nconst name = getItemName(id);"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "Fix"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ": Use Hob-native equivalents ("
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "filter"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " + "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "first"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ", "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "map"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ") or pre-compute values into a plain JS data structure and do synchronous lookups."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "invoke"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " Arg Order"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "invoke"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " calls a method on a JS object:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": ";; Correct: obj.method(arg) \n(invoke obj \"method\" arg)\n\n;; WRONG: does method[arg](), not obj.method(arg)\n(invoke (dom-get obj :method) arg)"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "invoke"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " Converts Args via "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "hobToJs"
          }
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "All arguments (but NOT the object) go through "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "hobToJs"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ", which converts non-DOM, non-primitive objects to plain "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "{}"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " by iterating "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "Object.entries"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ". This destroys browser API objects that have internal slots:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": ";; BROKEN — History object loses internal slots when passed as arg\n(invoke some-fn \"call\" null history)\n\n;; Fix — pass browser objects as the invocation target, not as args\n(invoke history \"pushState\" state \"\" url)"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "Rule"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ": Never pass "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "History"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ", "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "Location"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ", "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "Navigator"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ", or other browser API objects as "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "invoke"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " arguments. Pass them as the object (first argument) instead."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Morphdom Keeps Old Handlers"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "When morphdom patches the DOM after a Hob view re-render, it keeps the old element's event handlers rather than transferring new ones from the discarded "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "toEl"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " tree. This is correct because:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "morphdom keeps "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "fromEl"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " (the live DOM) and discards "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "toEl"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " (the fresh render)"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Old handlers have correct DOM references to the kept elements"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Handler logic is identical across renders; data is fetched fresh via "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "get-item"
              }
            ]
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "Do NOT"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " transfer "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "__hobEvents"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " in "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "onBeforeElUpdated"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " — new handlers capture refs to the discarded DOM tree."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Selector Pins"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Once a selector is registered via "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "(get-item id :select fn)"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " for an item, later bare "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "(get-item id)"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " calls on the same item don't widen the selector. The first selector registration is the contract."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "This means: put your selector on the primary "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "get-item"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " call, not on a secondary lookup."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "data-sort-key"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " for Morphdom Identity"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Always add "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "data-sort-key"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " (or another stable attribute) to elements rendered in loops — wrappers, pills, list items, etc. Without this, morphdom matches elements by position, causing mismatched updates when items are reordered."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "[:div {:data-sort-key item-id} ...]"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Hob Functions Can't Replace Sync APIs"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Some browser/JS APIs require synchronous callbacks:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "history.pushState"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " / "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "history.replaceState"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " (must be called synchronously in response to user action)"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "Array.sort"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " comparators"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "JSON.stringify"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " replacers"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Event handler return values (e.g., "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "beforeunload"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ")"
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "For these, write a JS library item that provides the synchronous interface. Example: "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "iframe-nav-tracker"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " patches "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "pushState"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " synchronously because Hob's async functions can't."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "sexp2ast.py"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " Unicode Limitation"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The s-expression to AST converter doesn't handle "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "\\uXXXX"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " escape sequences. Use literal Unicode characters in "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": ".hob"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " files instead of escape sequences."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "See Also"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
